item.title: [+1703] Done Deal: Conan O'Brien Seals $45M Deal to Leave 'Tonight'
item.description: NBC said Thursday it has reached a $45 million deal with Conan O'Brien for his exit from the Tonight Show, allowing Jay Leno to return to the late-night program he hosted for 17 years. Under the deal, which came seven months after O'Brien took the reins from Leno, O'Brien will get more than $33 million, NBC said. The rest will go to his staff.

item.title: [+1208] YouTube Rolls Out New Video Player, Adobe Flash Not Required
item.description: YouTube has just revealed that it is rolling out a new video player that supports HTLM5, one that can be accessed via YouTube’s TestTube idea incubator. An HTML5 video player will allow videos to be viewed without Adobe's Flashplayer plug-in, videos will load faster and developers will be able to build all kinds of other intriguing features.
